---
title: Speedy Refried Bean & Egg Burritos with Pepper Jack & Hot Sauce
description: If you’re ready to break ties with cold cereal for breakfast or a soggy sandwich for lunch, this warm, delicious, and filling 15-minute vegetarian breakfast burrito is the answer! You’ll scramble eggs with crème fraîche, scallion, and tomato (all in your microwave!), then layer onto warm flour tortillas along with creamy refried black beans and zesty pepper jack cheese. Top with more fresh scallion and tomato, then drizzle with tangy hot sauce, roll ’em up and serve, or refrigerate them for tomorrow’s breakfast or lunch. They’re a perfectly portable meal to-go!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/651320cd3cb5229806dac62b-c493eb20.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/651320cd3cb5229806dac62b.pdf
course: main course
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/speedy-refried-bean-egg-burritos-651320cd3cb5229806dac62b
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Central America
nutrition:
  calories: 650 kcal
