  sugar: 5 g
  protein: 29 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 1800 mg
---

Wash and dry produce.

Dice @tomato{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice half the @scallions{2} (all for 4 servings).

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, whisk together @crème fraîche{2%tbsp} and 2 TBSP water
(4 TBSP for 4 servings) until smooth and creamy. (TIP: If mixture is too thick, add
another splash of water.) Whisk in @eggs{2} and @salt{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4) until thoroughly
combined, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add half the tomato and half the sliced scallions to bowl. Cover with #plastic wrap{};
microwave, stirring halfway through, until eggs are puffed and cooked through,
~{1-2%minutes}. TIP: Check eggs after ~{1%minute}, then continue microwaving in 30-second
intervals until done.

While eggs cook, place each @flour tortillas{2} on a separate #microwave-safe plate{}. Spread a
thick layer of @Old El Paso Refried Black Beans{16%oz} on the bottom two-thirds of each
tortilla; evenly sprinkle with @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup}. TIP: You may not use all the refried beans.

Working in batches, microwave cheese-topped tortillas until beans are warmed
through and cheese begins to melt, ~{40-60%seconds}.

Lay cheese-topped tortillas on a clean work surface. Carefully remove plastic wrap
from bowl with scrambled eggs (bowl and contents will be hot!); divide eggs,
remaining tomato, and remaining sliced scallions between tortillas; drizzle with as
much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like.

Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides
toward filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form burritos.

Divide burritos between plates and serve.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.